label: flash flooding
definition: Flash flooding is a process in which low-lying land is inundated with water for a short period of time and are usually the result of precipitation or a breach in the container of a water body.

label: informal settlement
definition: A settlement which is not associated with or directed by official planning processes and which typically lacks municipal services and infrastructure such as sanitation, water services, and waste management services.

label: permission to access
definition: A disposition of an environmental system to allow an entity to approach and use a resource.

label: main group molecular entity
definition: A molecular entity containing one or more atoms from any of groups 1, 2, 13, 14, 15, 16, 17, and 18 of the periodic table.

label: independent continuant
definition: A continuant that is a bearer of quality and realizable entity entities, in which other entities inhere and which itself cannot inhere in anything.

label: ownership
definition: A process in which a person or organization, the owner, exercises their right to use, sell, rent, or gift an object.

label: owner role
definition: A role that inheres in a person and is realized in processes of exercising the right to use, occupy, sell, rent, or gift an object (such as a parcel of land).

label: flood
definition: An unusual accumulation of water above the ground caused by high tide, heavy rain, melting snow or rapid runoff from paved areas.

label: landslide process
definition: A landslide is a process whereby a large mass of earth and rocks moves down a hill or a mountainside.

label: sustainable development goal indicator value
definition: A data item which represents a sustainable development goal indicator in some quantitative or qualitative system of measurement.

label: employer role
definition: A role that inheres in a person or organization in virtue of the fact the bearer specifies actions to be performed for remuneration by one or more persons that bear an employee role.

label: health care service
definition: A service that promotes, secures, and maintains health care rights and the processes that realize them.

label: drinking water
definition: Drinking water is water which may be consumed by humans with no adverse effects on their health.

label: chalcogen molecular entity
definition: Any p-block molecular entity containing a chalcogen.

label: vulnerability towards flooding
definition: A vulnerability borne by an entity which may be impacted by flooding.

label: city
definition: Incorporated populated place.

label: s-block molecular entity
definition: An s-block molecular entity is a molecular entity containing one or more atoms of an s-block element.

label: lava flow process
definition: A process in which a volume of lava emitted during an effusive eruption moves along a solid surface.

label: exposure to contaminated water
definition: An exposure process in which an the processes executed by an entity are causally connected to those executed by a portion of contaminated water.

label: resilience
definition: A disposition of an entity to recover its previous composition, qualities, and functionality following some perturbation.

label: water vapour
definition: Water vapour is a vapour which is the gas phase of water.

label: established and operational policy
definition: A policy which is actively being implemented and managed in some set of appropriate processes for a long enough time to be generally accepted and functional.

label: chemical entity
definition: A chemical entity is a physical entity of interest in chemistry including molecular entities, parts thereof, and chemical substances.

label: carbon dioxide emission process
definition: A carbon emission process is any environmental process which releases carbon dioxide gas into the atmosphere.

label: essential medicine
definition: A medicine that is necessary to meet the priority health-care needs of a population according to treatment prevalence, efficacy, safety, and comparative cost-effectiveness.

label: exposure to contaminated lake flood
definition: An exposure process in which an the processes executed by an entity are causally connected to those executed by the floodwaters of a contaminated lake.

label: generically dependent continuant
definition: A continuant that is dependent on one or other independent continuant bearers. For every instance of A requires some instance of (an independent continuant type) B but which instance of B serves can change from time to time.

label: cabon dioxide emission
definition: A volume of carbon dioxide gas emitted by a carbon dioxide emission process.

label: vulnerability
definition: A disposition of an entity to undergo change, usually negative or undesirable change, in response to some exposure.

label: collection of organisms
definition: A material entity that consists of two or more organisms, viruses, or viroids.

label: right bearer
definition: A organism or organization that is the bearer of a right.

label: risk of flooding
definition: The risk that a bearer realises its vulnerability towards flooding when participating in a process which exposes the bearer to a flooding hazard.

label: carbon-bearing gas emission process
definition: A carbon emission process is any environmental process which outputs a carbon-bearing gas.

label: molecular entity
definition: Any constitutionally or isotopically distinct atom, molecule, ion, ion pair, radical, radical ion, complex, conformer etc., identifiable as a separately distinguishable entity.

label: resilience strengthening process
definition: A process which increases an entity's disposition to recover its previous composition, qualities, and functionality following some perturbation.

label: anthropogenic geographic feature
definition:
An anthropogenic geographic feature is a geographic feature
resulting from the influence of human beings on nature.

label: asset
definition: An independent continuant under the control of some person or organisation which confers an economic benefit in some economic system.

label: mudflow
definition: A mudflow is a form of mass wasting which involves very rapid to extremely rapid surging flow of debris that has become partially or fully liquified by the addition of significant amounts of water to clay-rich source material.

label: coast
definition: A coast is the area where land meets the sea, ocean, or lake.

label: material intensity of an economy
definition: A data item which represents the ratio of domestic material consumption to gross domestic product at constant prices.

label: deforestation
definition: The removal of forest and undergrowth to, for example, increase the surface of arable land or to use the timber for construction or industrial purposes.

label: p-block molecular entity
definition: A main group molecular entity that contains one or more atoms of a p-block element.

label: atmospheric carbon dioxide
definition: Atmospheric carbon dioxide is an environmental material composed of carbon dioxide in its gaseous form present in the atmosphere.

label: hazard disposition
definition: A disposition of an entity to cause harm or damage to another entity.

label: quality
definition: A dependent entity that inheres in a bearer by virtue of how the bearer is related to other entities

label: terrestrial biome
definition: A biome that applies to the terrestrial realm.

label: energy intensity
definition: A data item which represents the ratio between the gross inland consumption of energy and gross domestic product calculated for a calendar year.

label: waste material
definition: A material which is not the desired output of a process and which is typically the input of a process which removes it from its producer (e.g. a disposal process).

label: cropland biome
definition: A cropland biome is an anthropogenic terrestrial biome which is primarily used for agricultural activity and which contains no village or larger human settlement.

label: urban biome
definition: An urban biome is a dense settlement biome which has been urbanised.

label: inorganic molecular entity
definition: A molecular entity that contains no carbon.

label: dense settlement biome
definition: A dense settlement biome is an anthropogenic terrestrial biome which is primarily used for human habitation, recreation, and industry within built structures with little other land use.

label: protruding out of
definition: A quality inhering into a bearer by virtue of the bearer's extending out above or beyond its surface or boundary and outwards in relation to the physical space occupied by another entity.

label: waste water
definition: Water that has been adversely affected in quality by anthropogenic influence.

label: time
definition: A quality in which events occur in sequence.

label: protruding
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's extending out above or beyond a surface or boundary.

label: village
definition: A village is a clustered human settlement or community, larger than a hamlet but smaller than a town, with a population ranging from a few hundred to a few thousand. Though often located in rural areas, the term urban village is also applied to certain urban neighbourhoods. Villages are normally permanent, with fixed dwellings; however, transient villages can occur. Further, the dwellings of a village are fairly close to one another, not scattered broadly over the landscape, as a dispersed settlement.

label: material extraction process
definition: A planned process during which a portion of environmental material is removed from a material entity.

label: tourism
definition: A process in which a visitor travels to and stays in places outside their usual environment for not more than one consecutive year for leisure, business and other purposes. All the activities performed by the visitor in preparation for and during their trip are parts of this process.

label: unemployed
definition: A person or population that is not employed, but eligible for and currently seeking employment.

label: environmental feature
definition: A material entity which determines an environmental system.

label: essential service
definition: A service which is necessary to sustain human life.

label: atmospheric ozone
definition: Atmospheric ozone is an environmental material primarily composed of ozone in its gaseous form and present in the atmosphere.

label: owner
definition: A person or organization that participates in an ownership process wherein they realize their role as owner by exercising their right to use, sell, rent, or gift an object.

label: afforestation
definition: Establishment of a new forest by seeding or planting of nonforested land.

label: asset role
definition: A role inhering in an independent continuant which is realized by conferring an economic benefit to the person or organization which controls it in some economic system.

label: safe
definition: A low risk of entities in some environment to realize their hazard disposition towards humans.

label: environmental system
definition: A system which has the disposition to environ one or more material entities.

label: areal flooding
definition: Areal flooding is a flooding process in which flat or low-lying areas become inundated with water due to water input exceeding infiltration, evaporation, or run off.

label: process
definition: An occurrent that has temporal proper parts and for some time t, p s-depends_on some material entity at t.

label: populated place
definition: Place or area with clustered or scattered buildings and a permanent human population.

label: young
definition: An age which is relatively low.

label: sustainable access system
definition: A system that provides access to some resource in a sustainable manner. That is, the system provides someone or something the ability, right, and permission to approach and use some resource in a way that will not irreversibly exhaust the resources on which the system depends.

label: ability to access
definition: The disposition of an environmental system to physically provide a resource to the consumer or user of that resource.

label: ocean
definition: Continuous saline-water bodies that surround the continents and fill the Earth's great depressions.

label: quality of a gas
definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting the physical characteristics of an entity consisting of particles that have neither a defined volume nor defined shape.

label: right of access
definition: A disposition of a human societal system to recognise and protect, through various means, the ability of an entity to approach and use a resource.

label: physical object quality
definition: A quality which inheres in a continuant.

label: material input per capita
definition: A data item which represents the ratio of material input and total population.

label: watercourse
definition: A flowing body of water.

label: weapons test site
definition: A region at which weapons, typically military, are tested.

label: position
definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's spatial location relative to other objects in the vicinity.

label: material footprint per capita
definition: A data item which represents the ratio of material footprint and total population.

label: natural capital
definition: A collection of material entities which is composed of material natural assets and the ecosystem services which depend on them.

label: lake
definition: A body of water or other liquid of considerable size contained on a body of land.

label: sustainable development goal
definition: An objective specification which describes the endpoint of a development process following the Sustainable Development Agenda for 2030 plan specification.

label: educator role
definition: A role that inheres in a human and is realized in the process of imparting knowledge and skill to others.

label: biome
definition: A biome is an environmental system to which resident ecological communities have evolved adaptations.

label: use of a resource
definition: A process in which a resource is consumed or confers some benefit to the user.

label: elemental molecule
definition: A molecule all atoms of which have the same atomic number.

label: effusive eruption
definition: An effusive eruption is a volcanic eruption during which lava flows onto the ground.

label: marine water body
definition: A significant accumulation of water which is part of a marine biome.

label: nuclear weapons test site
definition: A weapons test site at which nuclear weapons are, or have been, tested.

label: process of being educated
definition: A planned process wherein a person acquires knowledge or skill. It is part of an education process.

label: constructed feature
definition: A feature that has been constructed by deliberate human effort.

label: age
definition: A time quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of how long the bearer has existed.

label: flooding
definition: A general and temporary condition of partial or complete inundation of normally dry land areas from the overflow of inland and/or tidal waters, and/or the unusual and rapid accumulation or runoff of surface waters from any source. A great flow along a watercourse or a flow causing inundation of lands not normally covered by water.

label: human dwelling
definition: A self-contained constructed feature used by one or more households as a home, such as a house, apartment, mobile home, houseboat or other 'substantial' structure. A dwelling typically includes nearby outbuildings, sheds etc. within the curtilage of the property, excluding any 'open fields beyond'. It has significance in relation to search and seizure, conveyancing of real property, burglary, trespass, and land use planning.

label: riverine flooding
definition: Riverine flooding is a process in which the flow rate of river water exceeds the capacity of its channel, thus flooding neighbouring land. Bends and meanders in a river channel are particularly disposed to such flooding.

label: recycling process
definition: A process in which some input bearing a waste role is consumed to produce an output which bears a resource role.

label: sustainable development process
definition: A process in which the parts of a socio-economic-environmental system, as well as their interactions and qualities, transition to meet one or more sustainable development goals.

label: water body
definition: An accumulation of water of varying size.

label: hydrides
definition: Hydrides are chemical compounds of hydrogen with other chemical elements.

label: urban flooding
definition: Urban flooding is a flooding process in which land or property in a built environment, particularly in more densely populated areas, is inundated due to the rate of water input exceeding that of water drainage provided by the environment's drainage systems.

label: mass wasting flow
definition: A mass wasting flow is a form of mass wasting during which the moving materials behave similarly to a flowing fluid. Water, air and ice are often involved in enabling fluidlike motion of the material.

label: mass wasting
definition: Mass wasting is the geomorphic process by which solid environmental material such as soil, sand, regolith, and/or rock move downslope typically as a mass, largely under the force of gravity, but frequently affected by water and water content as in submarine environments and mudslides.

label: lotic water body
definition: A lotic water body is a water body in which the accumulated water, in its totality, is flowing.

label: sewage
definition: Wastewater that is contaminated with feces or urine,

label: explosive eruption
definition: An explosive eruption is a volcanic process in which pressurised magma is violently expelled and froths into volcanic ash. Explosive eruptions can eject a cloud of rocks, dust, gas, and pyroclastic material  which may then collapse, creating a pyroclastic flow of hot volcanic matter.

label: employee
definition: A person that bears an employee role.

label: tectonic earthquake
definition: A tectonic earthquake is an earthquake caused by the release of elastic strain. A tectonic earthquake occurs when strains in rock masses have accumulated to a point where the resulting stresses exceed the strength of the rocks, and sudden fracturing results.

label: lentic water body
definition: A lentic water body is a water body in which the accumulated water, in its totality, has very little to no directed flow.

label: approaching a resource
definition: A process in which a potential consumer of a resource decreases their spatial distance to that resource, acting out of the right, permission, and ability of access.

label: secure right
definition: A right which is protected by a sustainable system.

label: anthropogenic environmental material
definition: Anthropogenic material in or on which organisms may live.

label: industrialisation
definition: A process which results in manufacturing becoming the predominant economic activity within a nation or region.

label: resource
definition: A material or immaterial entity which may confer benefit to its user or consumer.

label: exposure to contaminated environmental material
definition: An exposure process in which an the processes executed by an entity are causally connected to those executed by a portion of contaminated environmental material.

label: riverine flood
definition: A riverine flood is a flood which is formed as a result of a river's flow rate exceeding the capacity of its channel.

label: resource role
definition: A role which is realized by conferring some benefit to its consumer.

label: material entity
definition: An independent continuant that is spatially extended whose identity is independent of that of other entities and can be maintained through time.

label: specifically dependent continuant
definition: A continuant that inheres in or is borne by other entities. Every instance of A requires some specific instance of B which must always be the same.

label: elemental molecular entity
definition: A molecular entity all atoms of which have the same atomic number.

label: continuant
definition: An entity that exists in full at any time in which it exists at all, persists through time while maintaining its identity and has no temporal parts.

label: megathrust earthquake
definition: A megathrust earthquake is a tectonic earthquake which occurs at subduction zones at destructive plate boundaries (convergent boundaries). These interplate earthquakes are the planet's most powerful, with moment magnitudes that can exceed 9.0.

label: hydroxides
definition: Hydroxides are chemical compounds containing a hydroxy group or salts containing hydroxide (OH(-)).

label: wealth
definition: A data item which represents the total value of the assets under the control of a person, population or organisation.

label: coastal flood
definition: A coastal flood is a flood which is formed as a result of large amounts of water from marine water bodies or large lakes being transported to usually dry land by displacement processes such as high winds or seismic activity.

label: education
definition: A planned process wherein knowledge and skill is imparted.

sturzstrom
definition: A sturzstrom is a landslide consisting which has a great amount of kinetic energy resulting in greater horizontal movement when compared to its initial vertical drop â€” as much as 20 or 30 times the vertical distance. By contrast a normal landslide will typically travel a horizontal distance that is less than twice the distance that the material has fallen.

label: habitability
definition: A quality of a human dwelling by virtue of its dispositions to provide for its inhabitants: physical safety, adequate space, protection against the elements and other hazards to health and structure.

label: exposure to flood
definition: An exposure process in which an the processes executed by an entity are causally connected to those executed by a flood.

label: population
definition: A collection of organisms, all of the same species, that live in the same place.

label: polyatomic entity
definition: Any molecular entity consisting of more than one atom.

label: physical quality
definition: A quality of a physical entity that exists through action of continuants at the physical level of organisation in relation to other entities.

label: inadequate housing
definition: A human dwelling that lacks any one of the following: access to basic services, affordability, habitability, security of tenure, or accessibility.

label: social protection service
definition: A service that promotes, secures, and maintains socio-economic rights.

label: waste role
definition: A role that is realized in some process wherein the bearer is discarded or not utilized further.

label: heteroatomic molecular entity
definition: A molecular entity consisting of two or more chemical elements.

label: rangeland biome
definition: A rangeland biome is an anthropogenic terrestrial biome which is primarily used for the rearing and grazing of livestock.

label: desertification
definition: a type of land degradation in which a relatively dry land region becomes increasingly arid, typically losing its bodies of water as well as vegetation and wildlife.

label: atmospheric water vapour
definition: Atmospheric water vapour is water vapour that is part of an atmosphere.

label: rural settlement
definition: A settlement which has lower population density than a town, city, or other urban environment and is primarily used for agricultural or pastoral activity.

label: good ambient water quality
definition: An ambient water quality value which is specified when the water sampled from water bodies in a specified area poses little or no risk to normal ecosystem functioning or human health.

label: coastal flooding
definition: Coastal flooding is a process in which normally dry, low-lying land near a coast is flooded by sea water.

label: quality of a liquid
definition: A physical quality inhering in an entity exhibiting the physical characteristics of an amorphous (non-crystalline) form of matter between a gas and a solid that has a definite volume, but no definite shape.

label: fragile state
definition: A state which has an elevated risk towards a loss of centralized government control and protection, or a lowered resilience to perturbation, or an inability to maintain basic services, or a lack of social equality.

label: sparsely populated settlement
definition: A settlement with a low density of buildings and inhabitants.

label: ecological community
definition: A collection of organisms of at least two different species, living in a particular area.

label: geological subsidence
definition: A subsidence process is a geomorphologic process in which a surface shifts downward relative to a datum such as sea-level.

label: storm surge process
definition: A storm surge process is a coastal flooding process which is caused by low pressure weather systems such as tropical cyclones and strong extratropical cyclones, the severity of which is affected by the shallowness and orientation of the water body relative to storm path, and the timing of tides.

label: domestic resource consumption
definition: A resource consumption value which pertains to the environmental systems which overlap with a national economic system.

label: realizable entity
definition: A specifically dependent continuant  that inheres in continuant  entities and are not exhibited in full at every time in which it inheres in an entity or group of entities. The exhibition or actualization of a realizable entity is a particular manifestation, functioning or process that occurs under certain circumstances.

label: land consumption process
definition: A process in which natural ecosystems present over an expanse of land are removed and replaced with anthropogenic ecosystems.

label: volcanic eruption
definition: A volcanic process is a process during which lava, tephra (ash, lapilli, volcanic bombs and blocks), and assorted gases are expelled from a volcanic vent or fissure.

label: net permanent forest loss
definition: A data item about some process of forest loss and which represents a negative change in forest area over a sufficiently long time period.

label: role
definition: A realizable entity  the manifestation of which brings about some result or end that is not essential to a continuant  in virtue of the kind of thing that it is but that can be served or participated in by that kind of continuant  in some kinds of natural, social or institutional contexts.

label: inclusive
definition: A dependent continuant inhering in a bearer by virtue of that bearer having a range of entities, identified by a policy or regulatory specification, as parts or participants.

label: old
definition: An age which is relatively high.

label: polluted lake
definition: A lake which has concentrations of environmental contaminants high enough to harm the ecosystems associated with it.

label: inclusive wealth
definition: A wealth value which is the sum of human, manufactured, natural, and health capital assets.

label: rural area
definition: An area which is outside of a town, city, or urban area. Rural areas are primarily used for agriculture or pastoralism and may contain rural settlements.

label: process of educating
definition: A planned process wherein a person imparts knowledge or skill to one or more people. It is part of an education process.

label: metotsunami
definition: A meteotsunami is a tsunami caused by atmospheric processes and differences in air pressure.

label: important site
definition: An environmental zone which contains, as determined by an officially mandated selection process, one or more ecosystems which include, as parts, ecological communities of global significance for conservation due to their vulnerability and irreplaceability.

label: employed
definition: A person or population that participates in employment processes during a specified time interval.

label: natural asset
definition: An asset which is the result of or itself an environmental process that has not been substantially altered by human activity.

label: public infrastructure
definition: The system of public works in a country, state or region, including roads, utility lines and public buildings.

label: water
definition: An environmental material primarily composed of dihydrogen oxide in its liquid form.

label: medicine role
definition: A role that inheres in a molecular entity and is realized in the process of preventing, treating, diagnosing, or studying disease or disorder.

label: resource consumption
definition: A data item which estimates the metric tonnage of resource materials imported into or extracted from an environmental system and used as input for economic processes in that system, minus the tonnage of materials exported from that system.

label: environmental zone
definition: An environmental zone is an environmental feature whose extent is determined by the presence or influence of one or more material entities or processes. An environmental zone may, itself, assume the role of an environmental feature.

label: river
definition: Natural freshwater surface streams of considerable volume and a permanent or seasonal flow, moving in a definite channel toward a sea, lake, or another river; any large streams, or ones larger than brooks or creeks, such as the trunk stream and larger branches of a drainage system.

label: system
definition: A material entity consisting of multiple components that are causally integrated.

label: illegal informal settlement
definition: A populated place where groups of housing units have been constructed on land that the occupants have no legal claim to, or occupy illegally, or where dwellings are not in compliance with current planning and building regulations.

label: exposure to coastal flood
definition: An exposure process in which the processes executed by an entity are causally connected to those executed by a coastal flood.

label: flash flood
definition: A flash flood is a flood formed by the rapid flooding of geomorphic low-lying areas. It may be caused by heavy rain associated with a severe thunderstorm, hurricane, tropical storm, or meltwater from ice or snow flowing over ice sheets or snowfields. Flash floods may also occur after the collapse of a natural ice or debris dam, or a human structure such as a man-made dam. Flash floods are distinguished from a regular flood by a timescale of less than six hours.

label: village biome
definition: A village biome is an anthropogenic terrestrial biome which contains settlements such as villages, towns, and/or small cities and which is primarily used for agricultural activity.

label: quality of a single physical entity
protected area
definition: An area of land and/or a body of water especially dedicated to the protection and maintenance of biological diversity, and of natural and associated cultural resources, and managed through legal or other effective means.

label: stream
definition: Linear body of water flowing on the Earth's surface.

label: occurrent
definition: An entity that has temporal parts and that happens, unfolds or develops through time.

label: vulnerability towards drowning
definition: A vulnerability borne by an entity which may be killed by drowning.

label: earthquake
definition: An earthquake is a process whereby part of the surface of a planet shakes due to the passage of seismic waves through rocks. Seismic waves are produced when some form of energy stored in a planet's crust is suddenly released. Elastic strain, gravity, chemical reactions, or even the motion of massive bodies can produce earthquakes.

label: employee role
definition: A role that inheres in a person and is realized in an employment process by performing actions for remuneration.

label: access to basic services
definition: A disposition of a person or population who bears the ability, right, and permission to utilize available basic services in the community in which they reside.

label: access
definition: A disposition that inheres in a person or population who bears the ability, right, and permission to approach and use an accessible resource.

label: material trade balance
definition: A data item that represents the resource material trade surplus or deficit in of a nation's economy and is calculated in physical units as total amount of resource materials import minus exports.

label: water-borne disease
definition: A disease which is transmitted via a medium composed of water.

label: dihydrogen
definition: An elemental molecule consisting of two hydrogens joined by a single bond.

label: collection of organisms of the same species
definition: A material entity that has as parts two or more organisms, viruses, or viroids of the same species and no members of any other species.

label: quality of a substance
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its constitution.

label: park
definition: A bounded area of land, or water, usually in its natural or semi-natural (landscaped) state and set aside for some purpose, usually to do with recreation or conservation.

label: illegal settlement
definition: A settlement on land that the inhabitants have no legal claim to or occupy illegally.

label: risk
definition: A disposition of a bearer to realise one or more of its vulnerabilities when participating in a process which exposes the bearer to one or more corresponding hazards.

label: basic service
definition: A service which is needed by humans to maintain their health and well-being, or enable economic, social, and cultural development.

label: material footprint
definition: "A data item which estimates the metric tonnage of resource materials required to serve the final demand of a nation and is computed as raw material equivalent of imports (RMEIM) plus domestic extraction (DE) minus raw material equivalents of exports (RMEEX)."

label: risk of drowning
definition: The risk that a bearer realises its vulnerability towards drowning when participating in a process which exposes the bearer to a drowning hazard.

label: employment
definition: A planned process wherein an employee performs actions that are specified by an employer for remuneration.

label: formal settlement
definition: A settlement which has been established and is managed through officially sanctioned processes and is recognised as legal by a competent authority.

label: edibility
definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to being fit to be eaten.

label: environmental contaminant
definition: Any minor or unwanted substance introduced into the environment that can have undesired effects.

label: student
definition: A person that bears an educatee role.

label: water
definition: An oxygen hydride consisting of an oxygen atom that is covalently bonded to two hydrogen atoms.

label: sustainable development indicator
definition: A state of one or more parts of a socio-economic-environmental system which represents the state of the entire system.

label: ambient water quality
definition: A value specification about the amount of total dissolved solids (TDS); percentage dissolved oxygen (% DO); dissolved inorganic nitrogen (DIN); dissolved inorganic phosphorus (DIP); and abundance of Escherichia coli (E. coli) in a volume of water sampled from water bodies in an area.

label: slum
definition: A slum is a heavily populated urban informal settlement with substandard housing in which households lack any one of the following: access to improved water, access to improved sanitation, sufficient-living area, durability of housing, or security of tenure.

label: access system
definition: An environmental system which provides access to some resource. That is, the system has the disposition to physically provide and allow use of a given resource and allows the user of that resource to exercise their right and permission to access the resource.

label: educatee role
definition: A role that inheres in a human and is realized in the process of acquiring knowledge and skill.

label: chemical role
definition: A role played by the molecular entity or part thereof within a chemical context.

label: climate change
definition: The long-term fluctuations in temperature, precipitation, wind, and all other aspects of the Earth's climate. External processes, such as solar-irradiance variations, variations of the Earth's orbital parameters (eccentricity, precession, and inclination), lithosphere motions, and volcanic activity, are factors in climatic variation. Internal variations of the climate system, e.g., changes in the abundance of greenhouse gases, also may produce fluctuations of sufficient magnitude and variability to explain observed climate change through the feedback processes interrelating the components of the climate system.

label: rural
definition: Any entity associated with a rural settlement or area.

label: reforestation
definition: The planting of trees in areas in where forests have previously been cleared.

label: tsunami
definition: A tsunami is a process during which a series of waves is generated in a water body, typically an ocean or large lake, by the displacement of a large volume of water. Earthquakes, volcanic eruptions and other underwater explosions (including detonations of underwater nuclear devices), landslides, glacier calvings, meteorite impacts and other disturbances above or below water all have the potential to generate a tsunami.

label: medicine
definition: A material entity that is used in the process of preventing, treating, diagnosing, or studying disease or disorder.

label: storm surge
definition: A storm surge is a coastal flood which is caused by low-pressure weather systems such as tropical cyclones and strong extratropical cyclones, the severity of which is affected by the shallowness and orientation of the water body relative to storm path, and the timing of tides.

label: rural population
definition: A population of humans that lives in a rural settlement or rural area.

label: affordable
definition: A quality of an entity by virtue of it having a cost within the financial means of a person who has a median income.

label: exposure
definition: A process in which the processes executed by one entity are causally connected to those executed by another.

label: anthropogenic terrestrial biome
definition: An anthropogenic terrestrial biome is a terrestrial biome which has community structures determined by human activity.

label: sea
definition: A large expanse of saline water usually connected with an ocean.

label: ash fall process
definition: An ash fall process is a process in which volcanic ash formed during an explosive volcanic eruption, phreatomagmatic eruption, or during material transport in pyroclastic density currents is pulled towards the planetary surface by gravity.

label: sustainable development target
definition: A threshold value of a sustainable development indicator or a set of threshold values of several such indicators towards or beyond which corresponding indicator values from a socio-economic-environmental system should tend in order to meet a sustainable development goal.

label: direct material input
definition: A data item that estimates the metric tonnage of all resource materials which are input for the production and consumption activities of a nation's economy and is calculated by adding used domestic extraction with imported materials.

label: material trade balance per capita
definition: A data item which represents the ratio of material trade balance and total population.

label: role
definition: A role is particular behaviour which a material entity may exhibit.

label: land degradation
definition: A process which diminishes the functioning of an ecosystem located on land.

label: environmental material
definition: A portion of environmental material is a fiat object which forms the medium or part of the medium of an environmental system.

label: quality of a solid
definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting the physical characteristics of an entity characterized by particles arranged such that their shape and volume are relatively stable.

label: molecule
definition: Any polyatomic entity that is an electrically neutral entity consisting of more than one atom.

label: lahar
definition: A lahar is a type of mudflow or debris flow composed of a slurry of pyroclastic material, rocky debris, and water. The material flows down from a volcano, typically along a river valley.

label: dense settlement
definition: A settlement with a high density of buildings and inhabitants.

label: avalanche
definition: An avalanche is a rapid flow of snow down a sloping surface.
